<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romania's Government Presents Anti-Crisis Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The basis of the economic
development consists in a stable national currency, healthy
banking system to finance economic growth, a simpler and more
stable legislation to improve business environment, Romanian State
Minister Valeriu Stoica said on Wednesday, presenting the
anti-crisis Program of the government.
</P>
<P>
Romania was in a difficult moment, in an economic recession and
if it did not take action quickly it would run the risk of a deep
crisis, Stoica warned at President Emil Constantinescu's meeting
with leaders of parliamentary parties, representatives of the
civil society.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time in Romania and in its political life that
the Government, the parliamentary majority, the parliamentary
opposition and three major segments of the civil society, namely
the labour unions, the business media organizations and the civic
organizations, meet together, noticed the media.
</P>
<P>
"This meeting is a sign of political stability that could avoid
the crisis and allow a healthy economic growth," said Stoica, who
is concurrently minister of justice.
</P>
<P>
The anti-crisis Program presented under the title ''For a
healthy economic growth'' said there were big delays in the reform
process and a ''lot of overdue loan payments'' have been
accumulated since 1990. State sector is still considerable, the
gross domestic product decreased, exports came to a standstill,
the commercial deficit was big.
</P>
<P>
Referring to anti-crisis measures, Stoica said that they will
blend macro-stabilization policies with specific decisions foe
each sector: restructuring of state-run companies and national
utilities (power, gas, thermal energy, railways), relaunch of
farming, boosting export.
</P>
<P>
As for the banking sector, the main measures envisaged are
BANCOREX (Foreign Trade Bank) restructuring, reinvigorating the
Farming Bank and preparing it to go private, and starting sell-off
procedures in Romania's Commercial Bank, with all these to be
efficiently mediated by the newly established Agency for
Capitalization of Bank Assets.
</P>
<P>
Promoting new regulations on privatization procedures, to speed
up the process and firmly encourage domestic capital, accelerating
restructuring of industrial companies and public utilities,
boosting export are some other targets of the new government
program.
</P>
<P>
As for the farming, the main steps to be taken are granting
credits accessible to farmers and developing an efficient and
convenient equipment purchase system.
</P>
<P>
Romania's government is well-aware of the hardship suffered by
the populace as well as of the seriousness of the situation, the
end of the program presented by Stoica read. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
