<HEADLINE> Ugandan to Chair G-77 Chamber of Commerce, Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Chairman of Uganda National
Chamber of Commerce and Trade, Boney Katatumba, has been elected
to chair the G-77 Chamber of Commerce and Industry (G77-CCI) of
the developing countries.
</P>
<P>
This was announced Wednesday afternoon at the closing of the
three-day General Assembly of the G77-CCI here at the
International Conference Center by Moses Ali, second deputy prime
minister and minister of tourism, trade and industry
</P>
<P>
Katatumba takes over as the new chairperson from Tariq Sayeed
of Pakistan for a two-year term of office.
</P>
<P>
The incoming chairperson noted that during his term of office,
he will ensure that a trade and development bank is set up in
Nairobi, Kenya, as planned.
</P>
<P>
Moses Ali also pledged his government's continued support to
the G-77 which he said will include providing a good political
will and an enabling environment to the business sector.
</P>
<P>
The new chairman also called for cooperation among developing
countries, saying it is the only strategy of removing barriers
that have hindered development of marginalized countries.
</P>
<P>
The General Assembly of G77-CCI, the eighth of its kind, put
emphasis on bridging the information gap which will improve
technology transfer and increase efficiency of developing
countries.
</P>
<P>
The G77-CCI was founded in 1986 to strengthen South-South
cooperation in the wake of regionalism and the general assembly is
held every two years. The seventh general assembly was held in
Pakistan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
