<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 198,000 Goats, Sheep Smuggled out of Ethiopia Annually </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Ministry of
Agriculture announced Wednesday that about 198,000 goats and sheep
are smuggled out of the country annually.
</P>
<P>
The ministry was quoted by the official Ethiopian News Agency
as saying that an average of 66,000 live goats and sheep were
exported every year which is only a third of which is smuggled out
the country.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia has the largest population of husbandry in Africa with
about 42 million goat and sheep population.
</P>
<P>
The country produces annually 123,000 metric tons and 99,000
metric tons of mutton and goat meat respectively and the stated
volume of mutton production accounts for 43 percent of the total
production in east Africa.
</P>
<P>
In addition, according to the ministry, Ethiopia exports a
total of 13, 000 metric tons of frozen mutton and goat meat every
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
