<DOCNO> XIE19990408.0017 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-07 18:48 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Continued Peace Talks Key to Mideast Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, April 7 (Xinhua) -- China on Wednesday called on all
the parties concerned in the Middle East peace process to
implement existing agreements, honor the promises made and
continue the peace talks so as to break the current deadlock.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng, visiting Chairman of the Standing Committee of the
National People's Congress (NPC) of China, stressed that China
has always been concerned with the situation in the Middle East
and the Mideast peace process.
</P>
<P>
"We believe that it is the desire of the peoples and countries
in the region to realize peace in the Middle East. A peaceful
Middle East is in the interests of all the countries in the
region and is conducive to world peace and development," he said.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng made the remarks during his talks with Syrian President
Hafez al-Assad in Latakiya, a Mediterranean coastal city some 340
kilometers to the northwest of Damascus, the capital of Syria.
</P>
<P>
It was the strategic choice by the countries in the region to
try to solve the conflicts between Israel and the Arab nations
through peace talks, Li said, adding that despite the twists and
turns in the seven-year-long peace process, it was irreversible.
</P>
<P>
It is the key to breaking the current impasse in the peace
process to implement all the U.N. Security Council resolutions
regarding the Mideast issues, to carry out all the agreements
which the parties concerned had reached and uphold the principle
of "land for peace," the top Chinese legislator said.
</P>
<P>
Syria is an important party in the peace process. And without
the participation by Syria, there would not be peace in real
sense in the region, he said.
</P>
<P>
Reaffirming China's stance to support the just cause of the
Arab nations to recover their lost land, Li said "No matter what
changes take place in the Middle East situation, this stance of
China will never change."
</P>
<P>
Assad reiterated Syria's position on the Middle East issues,
and highly appreciated China's efforts in seeking a just and fair
solution to the Middle East problems. He thanked China for
supporting the just cause of the Arab people.
</P>
<P>
On relations between China and Syria, Li Peng and Assad
agreed that it is necessary to increase exchanges between the
two countries in order to further promote a comprehensive
development of the bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng said that in recent years, there had been new
developments in the friendly cooperation between China and Syria.
China highly appreciates Syria's policies to actively foster its
ties with China and to adhere to the One-China stance, he said.
</P>
<P>
Assad said that the peoples of Syria and China had always
been standing shoulder to shoulder in the history of the
bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Noting that there occurred many new and complicated matters in
the world arena, the Syrian president said that all the developing
countries should keep united in order to meet all kinds of
challenges.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng said that it was the basis of China's foreign
policy to strengthen the unity and cooperation with other
developing countries.
</P>
<P>
This unity and cooperation are of particular importance in
the current world situation which is characterized by the trends
of multi-polarization and economic globalization, the Chinese leader
said.
</P>
<P>
Li arrived here late Tuesday afternoon on a three-day
official visit. He is to leave Damascus for Islamabad, Pakistan,
on Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
