BUCHAREST, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Romania welcomes Libyia's
decision to surrender two Libyan citizens for trial in the
Netherlands under the Scottish law, sources in the Foreign
Ministry said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Romania praised the international community's efforts to
kickstart legal proceedings against the two Libyan citizens, in
particular by UN Secretary-General Annan and the leaders of
South-Africa, Egypt and Saudi Arabia, said Simona Miculescu,
spokeswoman with the ministry.
</P>
<P>
Romania backed the American-British proposal last year to
settle the Lockerbie case in the Netherlans within its steady
campaign of condemning any form of terrorism.
</P>
<P>
Abdel Basset al-Megrahi, 47, and Al-Amin Khalifa Fahima, 43,
who had been suspected of having planted a bomb suitcase on board
of a Pan Am Boeing aircraft, were charged on Tuesday with the
murder of 259 passengers and crew aboard Pan Am Flight 103 and 11
on the ground who died when the airliner crashed at Lockerbie,
Scottland. 
