<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romania Cautious About Evaluating Belgrade's Announcement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Romania appreciates in principle
"any credible step" meant to lead to a political solution to the
Kosovo conflict, Romania's Foreign Ministry stressed on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Spokewoman with the ministry Simona Miculescu made the remark
to the press when referring to the decision of Belgrade
authorities to cease unilaterally the military actions in Kosovo
during Easter Holidays.
</P>
<P>
"Given the special complexity of the situation on the scene -
the information we have show a wide depopulation of the ethnic
Albanian segment in Kosovo - along with the political context
against which the announcement was made, we need to be cautious
about evaluating it", the spokewoman added.
</P>
<P>
"Certainly, a lasting solution to the conflict involves the
fulfillment of all the conditions the international community
imposed clearly", Simona Miculescu concluded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
