<HEADLINE> 9 Millions of Ethiopian Kids Vaccinated Against </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Ministry of
Health announced Wednesday that over nine million children were
vaccinated against polio in two rounds of immunization campaign
conducted across the nation in 1998.
</P>
<P>
Hiwot Mengistu, an official from the ministry said at a meeting
in Nazareth, some 90 kilometers southeast of capital Addis Ababa,
that nearly 100 percent performance was registered in the Amhara,
Oromiya, Southern People' s and Harari states.
</P>
<P>
However, in the Somali state, the performance is less than 50
percent, the Ethiopian News Agency quoted Hiwot as saying.
</P>
<P>
The ministry announced last year that 9,092,852 children under
the age of five years across this African country would be
vaccinated against polio in two rounds in 1998.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia is among the nine countries where some children are
still becoming paralyzed every year due to the wide spread of the
polio virus.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia has plans to eradicate the polio by the year 2,000.
</P>
<P>
This year's immunization program will center on areas where
polio immunization coverage is low, according to the meeting held
in Nazareth. 
</P>
