<HEADLINE> Top Seed Bumps out at Estoril Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Top-seeded Anke Huber of Germany
was bumped out of the Estoril Open at Oeiras on Wednesday, losing
to unseeded Hungarian Rita Kuti Kis 7-6 (11-9), 6-1.
</P>
<P>
Huber lost her first service game and went down to 1-5 in the
first set. She briefly rallied but then surrendered a 5-1 lead in
the tiebreak and collapsed in the second set.
</P>
<P>
Also in the women's competition Wednesday, No. 3 seed Anne
Kremer of Luxembourg edged past Spaniard Eva Bes 6-4, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Argentinian Mariana Diaz Oliva came back from a set down to
notch a surprise victory over defending champion Barbara Schwartz
of Austria, 1-6, 6-0, 6-1.
</P>
<P>
In the men's singles, six-seeded Spaniard Felix Mantilla
chalked up a 6-3, 6-2 second-round victory over Andrei Medvedev of
Ukraine, who won the tournament in 1993. 
