<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-07 15:59 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran's Daily Chief Terms Ban as Political Move </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Faezeh Hashemi, Managing Director
of the closed Iranian daily Zan Wednesday termed the ban on her
daily as a "political move" by the conservatives against the
moderates, main supporters of Iranian President Mohammad Khatami.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference, Hashemi said the order by the
revolutionary court to close down her daily was "illegal," adding
that the case of her daily should be investigated by the Ministry
of Culture and Islamic Guidance or the press court, not the
revolutionary court.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian revolutionary court Wednesday ordered to close
down the moderate Persian-language daily Zan (Women) until further
notice for publishing a letter of Farah Diba, the ousted Iranian
queen, on April 3 and a caricature on April 6 making fun of
"blood money."
</P>
<P>
Head of the Tehran revolutionary court Gholamhussein Rahbarpour
said that the mere publication of Farah's message on new Iranian
year started on March 21 was a "blatant anti-revolutionary act"
and publicity for the "vicious" (monarchical) regime.
</P>
<P>
However, Hashemi, daughter of former Iranian President Hashemi
Rafsanjani, argued that publishing part of Farah's message without
any comment did not mean that her daily confirmed the message or
propagated for Farah or the former Iranian Shah regime.
</P>
<P>
She also rejected charge that her daily published a caricature
to ridicule blood money, money paid by murderers to the family of
a victim as compensation.
</P>
<P>
The ban on the daily Zan can be seen as part of the campaigns
by the right-ring factions for the sixth Majlis election to be
held early next year, Hashemi said.
</P>
<P>
Local political observers noted that the ban on the daily Zan
indicated the start of a new round political quarrel between the
powerful conservatives, who still dominate most of the
country's state organs, and the moderates. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
