<HEADLINE> Belgium Offers Financial Aid to Tunisia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TUNIS, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Belgium on Wednesday delivered 3.3
million dinars (3 million U.S. dollars) to Tunisia to help the
country implement a rehabilitation project on the southern bank of
the Tunis Lake.
</P>
<P>
The money is the second instalment from a total allocation of
10 million dinars (9 million dollars) from Belgium to the project,
the Tunisia Africa News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Director General of the European Affairs Department of the
Tunisian Foreign Ministry Anwar Brais and Belgium Ambassador to
Tunisia John Francoin Brendaris signed a document on the delivery
of the money.
</P>
<P>
The project, with a total investment of 76 million dinars (69
million dollars), also got a Dutch contribution of 15.2 million
dinars (13.8 million dollars) and a credit of 18 million dinars
(16.4 million dollars) from the European Investment Bank.
</P>
<P>
The rehabilitation program is one of the major projects
undertaken by the Tunisian government before the new millennium.
</P>
<P>
It is designed to develop the real estate areas on the southern
bank of the Tunis Lake to give the capital Tunisia a face lift on
the Mediterranean coast. 
</P>
