<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz
Sharif and Vice President of Yemen Abdurabu Mansour Hadi expressed
their mutual desire here Wednesday to enlarge and deepen economic
cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Sharif and Hadi, who arrived here Tuesday on a two-day visit to
Pakistan, held wide-ranging discussions on issues of common
interest including aspects of bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders hoped that the upcoming meeting of
Pakistan-Yemen Joint Ministerial Commission in May would provide a
fresh opportunity to focus on measures to expand trade and other
forms of economic and technical cooperation.
</P>
<P>
