<HEADLINE> Russia's Duma Calls for Military Aid for Yugoslavia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Russia's State Duma, or the lower
house of parliament, voted overwhelmingly on Wednesday for a
resolution urging President Boris Yeltsin and his government to
provide military aid for Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Deputies in the house voted 279-34 for the non-binding
resolution, which also called for government delegations to visit
a number of countries, including Germany, France, Italy, Greece,
Romania, Bulgaria, India and Egypt, to explain Russia's opposition
to NATO military strikes on Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
The resolution urged the president and his government to
discuss and adopt necessary measures by April 15 for providing
weapons and spare parts for Yugoslavia and sending a military
delegation to the country. 
