<HEADLINE> Lions, Hyenas Locked in Fierce Fight in E. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 7 (Xinhua) -- A fierce fight between a pride
of lions and a herd of hyenas in east Hararghe of Ethiopia has
left six lions and thirty hyenas dead, the Ethiopian News Agency
said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted local police officer Corporal Seyoum Degefa
as saying that the fight, which broke out in the Gobele Desert
seven days ago, shows no sign of abatement.
</P>
<P>
"During the day time the beasts lurk in their den waiting for
the sun to set," the police officer said. "When dark settles,
they begin their deadly fight."
</P>
<P>
It is impossible to bring the noisy fierce fight to an end, he
said, adding that the combat zone is far away from the local
villages. 
</P>
