<HEADLINE> Li Peng's Visit to Further Fortify Sino-Pak Ties: Speaker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The forthcoming visit to
Pakistan by senior Chinese leader Li Peng will further fortify the
existing friendly and cooperative ties between Pakistan and China.
</P>
<P>
This was stated here Wednesday by Ellahi Bukhsh Soomro, speaker
of the National Assembly, during an exclusive interview with
Xinhua on the eve of Li Peng's visit to this South Asian nation.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng, chairman of the Standing Committee of the National
People's Congress (NPC) of China, will make a five-day official,
goodwill visit to Pakistan at the invitation of Soomro.
</P>
<P>
Soomro said that the exchanges of high-level visits between
Pakistan and China have been very frequent. They are important and
necessary in the changing world, and especially conducive to the
further strengthening of the relations between Pakistan and China.
</P>
<P>
"Each exchange of high-level visit brings our relations
closer," said the speaker, adding that Li Peng's forthcoming visit
to Pakistan will further cement the existing friendly and
cooperative relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Soomro said Li Peng is an old friend of Pakistan as he visited
Pakistan 10 years ago in his capacity of Chinese premier.
</P>
<P>
"Li Peng is an experienced and knowledgeable leader of a great
country which is a valued friend of Pakistan. I am eagerly looking
forward to his visit," he said.
</P>
<P>
Soomro noted that Pakistan and China have different social
systems, yet the friendship between the two countries has become a
model in the international community.
</P>
<P>
He is of the view that the contact and cooperation between
Pakistan's National Assembly and NPC of China will be further
increased in the days ahead.
</P>
<P>
Soomro spoke highly of China's reform and opening policy
initiated by late Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping. The speaker said
he first visited China in the late 60s, and since then he has
toured the neighbor at least six times.
</P>
<P>
"I witnessed the major developments which have taken place in
China during the last two decades," he said, adding that the
Chinese leadership has adopted correct policies in accordance with
China's specific conditions for building the socialist market
economy.
</P>
<P>
He noted that China now enjoys political stability and economic
development thanks to the foresight and sagacity of the Chinese
leadership.
</P>
<P>
The Pakistani government and people are very happy to see a
strong and prosperous China emerging, the speaker added.
</P>
<P>
China has made remarkable achievements in agriculture, industry
as well as in science and technological field, and is playing an
increasingly important role in the international community for
peace and stability, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan and China share a lot of commonalities, and always
help and support each other, he said.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his belief that Li Peng's visit will push the
Pakistan-China all-round partnership of cooperation towards the
21st century to a new high. 
</P>
</TEXT>
