<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Public Called On to Care for Elderly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian Deputy Speaker of
the House of People's Representatives, Petros Olango Wednesday
called upon the public to step up efforts geared toward
alleviating the social problems facing elder persons.
</P>
<P>
The deputy speaker made the call at a special festival held
here to observe this year's World Health Day which is being
celebrated Wednesday throughout the world under the theme of
"Active aging makes the difference."
</P>
<P>
Petros said that efforts deployed so far by the international
as well as local aid organizations and associations in support of
the Ethiopian elderly are minimal.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the federal constitution of the Horn of Africa
country ensures the rights of the elderly to have access to social
services and proper care, and urged the populace to respect and
care for the elderly.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the festival, which was jointly organized by the
World Health Organization and the Ethiopian Ministry of Health,
Yohannes Tadesse, head of the health service and training
department of the ministry, said that of the 580 million senior
people across the world, 355 million are living in the developing
countries.
</P>
<P>
He said this year's World Health Day theme inspires the elderly
to involve themselves more in socio-economic and political
activities. 
</P>
