a Turkish Airlines passenger plane crashed in southern Turkey, the
Anatolia News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The agency said the Boeing 737-400 plane named "Trakya" was
engulfed in fire soon after taking off from Adana Airport and
crashed near the Ceyhan town, 40 kilometers east of Adana,
southern Turkey. No passengers were on board.
</P>
