<HEADLINE> Sino-Italian Chemical Venture to Start Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 8 (Xinhua) -- A Sino-Italian sodium citrate
joint venture is expected to begin operation soon after the
approval of the State Administration for Industry and Commerce,
the Chinese partner of the venture said here today.
</P>
<P>
Yao Shouzhu, general manager of the Samic Pharmaceutical and
Chemical Co. Ltd., said that the company will produce 10,000 tons
of sodium citrate and other chemical products a year.
</P>
<P>
Sodium citrate is an important chemical material for
pharmaceutical, chemical, fodder and food processing industries.
China's annual demand for the product is estimated at 40,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
The project is jointly sponsored by Sanmenxia city of central
China's Henan Province and a chemical company in Milan with an
total investment of 53 million U.S. dollars.  
