<HEADLINE> Vietnamese Paper Urges Negotiation on Kosovo Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, April 8 (Xinhua) -- The official Communist Party of
Vietnam newspaper Nhan Dan (The People) Thursday urged the United
States and NATO to immediately end their military attack against
Yugoslavia and said negotiation is the only way to restore peace
in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
Nhan Dan said in a commentary that the Yugoslavian government
has once again expressed its goodwill and resolve to peacefully
settle the Kosovo crisis by declaring a unilateral cease-fire, and
preparing for a provisional accord to grant substantial autonomy
to the ethnic Albanians in Kosovo and a program for the return of
refugees.
</P>
<P>
The commentary, entitled "Stop War And Sit Down For
Negotiations, The Only Way To Restore Peace In Kosovo," said the
reason the United States and NATO rejected Yugoslavia's offer of
cease-fire was "arrogant of a group that prefers to use military
power to solve all issues."
</P>
<P>
The United States and NATO have insisted that the cease-fire
offer was "insufficient" and that before a cease-fire can be
considered, Yugoslavia must meet what they claim is "the demand
established by the international community," the paper said.
</P>
<P>
"The so-called demand by the international community referred
to by the U.S. and NATO is in fact an unreasonable demand raised
by NATO for Serbia and Yugoslavia to withdraw all their forces out
of Kosovo and accept NATO's scheme to deploy 28,000 infantry
troops in Yugoslavia to interfere in the internal affairs of that
sovereign nation," the daily pointed out.
</P>
<P>
By dismissing the cease-fire initiative and ignoring the public
demand for a political solution to the crisis, the U.S. and NATO
are continuing with their military escalation against Yugoslavia,
the daily said.
</P>
<P>
"The United States and NATO must put an immediate end to their
cruel military attack against Yugoslavia," the daily urged.
</P>
</TEXT>
