<HEADLINE> Zhu: China-U.S. Friendship Could Not be Undermined by Anybody </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji said
here Thursday that the friendship between China and the United
States could not be undermined by anybody and that problems
existing between the two countries could be solved through
friendly consultations.
</P>
<P>
Zhu, who is paying an eight-day official visit to the United
States, made the remarks at the welcoming ceremony on the South
Lawn at the White House.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese premier said that the friendship between China and
the United States is based on the three China-U.S. Joint
Communiques and the Joint China-U.S. Statement as well as solemn
commitments made by the two countries to each other.
</P>
<P>
"I don't think there is any problem or question between our two
countries that cannot be solved through friendly consultations,"
Zhu stressed.
</P>
<P>
He said that the two countries might have some disagreements
or differences, but only friends who can discuss and solve their
differences are good friends. 
</P>
