<HEADLINE> PBOC to Strengthen Financial Supervision </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 8 (Xinhua) -- The People's Bank of China (PBOC),
China's central bank, plans to establish an effective financial
supervision responsibility system to improve its overall
supervisory capacity. according to sources from PBOC branch
directors' quarterly meeting held here today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the meeting, PBOC Governor Dai Xianglong said that
fairly beneficial conditions and opportunities for reinforcing
financial supervision are in place, including government policies
concerning financial reform and rectification, the smooth
development of the PBOC's management system reform and the
accumulation of experience in preventing financial risks.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the PBOC and branches at all levels should
seize the opportunity to accelerate supervisory efforts and
attempt to establish an effective financial management system
within two years.
</P>
<P>
Effective supervision will help reduce the ratio of
nonperforming loans for state-owned commercial banks, promote the
healthy development of small to medium-sized financial
institutions and improve financial order, said Dai.
</P>
<P>
Participants discussed issues concerning the establishment of a
financial supervision responsibility system and analyzed China's
financial operations in the first quarter of the year.  
</P>
