<HEADLINE> Russia Pledges Work for Solution of Cyprus Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Russian envoy for Cyprus Vladimir
Tchizov reiterated here on Thursday that his country is committed
to finding a solution to the Cyprus issue.
</P>
<P>
Tchizov arrived here Wednesday night to discuss ways to
promote a Cyprus settlement and prepare the ground for the
visit of Russian Deputy Foreign Minister Alexander Avteyev, who
is due to arrive in Cyprus later Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Avteyev's visit takes lace within the framework of bilateral
relations while Tchizov's meetings here are part of Russia's
efforts to help find a Cyprus solution.
</P>
<P>
Speaking after a meeting with Cyprus' Foreign Minister Ioannis
Kasoulides, Tchizov said he previously visited Athens and Ankara,
and had contacts in Moscow with U.S. Special Coordinator Thomas
Miller.
</P>
<P>
He also said that upon his return to Moscow, he will meet
the European Union German presidency representative Detlev Graf
zu Rantzau and British representative for Cyprus Sir David
Hannay.
</P>
<P>
Tchizov will cross to the northern area of the Cyprus
island Thursday afternoon to meet Turkish Cypriot leader Rauf
Denktash.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus has been divided since 1974 when Turkish troops
invaded and controlled the northern third of the island in the
wake of a failed pro-Athens coup.
</P>
<P>
Russia has repeatedly called for a solution to the Cyprus
issue, in accordance with U.N. resolutions, providing for the
establishment of a bicommunal, bizonal federation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
