<HEADLINE> Shanghai Police Pursues Bank Robber </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Two men from neighboring Jiangsu
province robbed the Shanghai Bank earlier today.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the local police bureau reported that Jiang Guan
and Feng Dejun from the city of Lianyungang, Jiangsu Province,
robbed 10,000 yuan (1,200 US dollars) from the Chang'an Road
Branch of the Shanghai Bank. Jiang was apprehended immediately and
law enforcement officers recovered 1,700 yuan from him. Feng
escaped.
</P>
<P>
Sources indicate that today's bank robbery was the first in
Shanghai in the 1990s.
</P>
<P>
The two men entered the branch's business office this morning
at 09:45 (Beijing time) and fired two shots from handmade pistols.
The bank clerks immediately sounded the alarm, three of them
suffered slight injuries.
</P>
<P>
Law enforcement officers and a number of private citizens
responded to the alarm and apprehended Jiang. They seized two
pistols and nine bundles of explosives from the two robbers.
</P>
<P>
The public security bureau launched an extensive manhunt for
Feng. 
</P>
</TEXT>
