<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 8 (Xinhua) -- The State Forestry Administration
announced that firefighters successfully put out the forest fire
in north China's Shanxi Province at around 09:00 this morning.
</P>
<P>
Firefighters valiantly battled the blaze, with their efforts
aided by a successful cloud-seeding program carried out on
Wednesday night, confirmed the provincial forest fire fighting
headquarters.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,800 firefighters, including 200 forest wardens from
neighboring Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region, are closely
monitoring smoldering ashes, the headquarters said.
</P>
<P>
The fire erupted in the mountains near Fenyang City, Shanxi
Province on April 3 and spread rapidly to neighboring Wenshui
County on April 4.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-three people died battling the blaze which spread over
20,000 hectares.  
