<HEADLINE> NATO Preparing for Use of Troops: Canadian Defense Chief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Canada and its NATO allies are
actively planning for the possible deployment of ground troops in
Kosovo to force a peace settlement on the Yugoslav leadership,
Canadian Defense Minister Art Eggleton said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Eggleton said that the refugee crisis and the refusal of
Slobodan Milosevic, the president of Yugoslavia, to resume peace
talks despite heavy bombing has forced NATO to consider the option
of using ground forces.
</P>
<P>
