<HEADLINE> Nepal Holds Flower Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, April 8 (Xinhua) -- In a further effort to boost
floriculture in Nepal, a four-day flower fair opened here
Thursday, attracting 25 participants from the country.
</P>
<P>
Organizing Committee Chairman Shantosh Bickram Shah said his
country's share of the world's land area is no more than 0.1
percent but its share of the flowering plant species amounts to
over 2 percent.
</P>
<P>
A total of 7,183 species of plants have been identified in the
country and about 250 of them are endemic, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Himalayan kingdom has a favorable climate for floriculture.
Annual trade in flowers in the country is reportedly nearly five
million rupees (73,530 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The Floriculture Association Nepal aims to export flowers soon
on a trial basis. 
</P>
