capital last year the year, with exports to Taiwan standing at 150
million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Business people and officials from the two sides agreed that
the mainland and Taiwan are mutually complementary. They also
agreed that cross-Straits trade and cooperation should be further
expanded.
</P>
<P>
A number of speakers focused on whether or not Taiwan should
buy more agricultural products from the mainland. Various speakers
proposed that a quota system might be useful for controlling
related trade and protecting the interests of Taiwan farmers.
