<HEADLINE> New Government Building Unveiled in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Macao residents will find it easier
to go through some administrative formalities as an edifice
housing nine government departments was unveiled here today.
</P>
<P>
Situated in a downtown area, the building accommodates the
government departments in charge of public administration, housing,
translation of laws, judicial affairs, and various kinds of
registration related to birth, marriage, death, property, business
and vehicles.
</P>
<P>
Most of the departments used to lease offices from individual
proprietors and had to spend large sums of rent every year.
</P>
<P>
The Macao Posts and Telecommunications Department bought the
edifice last August with 408 million patacas (about 51 million U.S.
dollars). All the departments in the building should turn in
reasonable sums of rent.
</P>
<P>
The building has 33 stories, five of which are used as parking
lots. Local residents may enjoy great convenience as parking space
is rather limited in Macao.  
</P>
</TEXT>
