<HEADLINE> Cross-Straits Trade Witnesses Continuing Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The cross-Straits trade volume for the January-February period
hit 2.8 billion US dollars, up 7.7 percent on the 1998 period,
according to Customs Department statistics released at the ongoing
Third Trade Fair for Taiwan Goods.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that 41,748 Taiwan-funded projects have been
approved in the mainland, involving total investments of 41.6
billion US dollars. Taiwan ranks fourth in terms of overseas
investor in the mainland.
</P>
<P>
Mechanical and electrical machinery accounted for some 50
percent of products exported to Taiwan in 1998. The total value of
related products jumped 31.6 percent on the 1997 figure to 1.87
billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Foreign trade officials expressed optimism concerning the
further development of cross-Straits trade ties.
</P>
<P>
"A sharp increase in exports to Taiwan and rising investments
from the island province indicate the vast potential for economic
cooperation," said Wang Hui, an official with the Ministry of
Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation.  
