<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Joins Indian Ocean Rim Association </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh has become a member of
the Indian Ocean Rim Association for Regional Cooperation
(IOR-ARC), Bangladeshi Foreign Minister Abdus Samad Azad said here
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh was admitted as a new member of the group at the
second council of ministers' meeting of the IOR-ARC at Maputo,
Mozambique, on March 30-31 this year, he said.
</P>
<P>
Iran, Seychelles, Thailand and the United Arab Emirates also
joined the association at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The IOR-ARC, grouping Australia, India, Kenya, Mauritius, Oman,
Singapore, South Africa, Indonesia, Madagascar, Malaysia,
Mozambique, Sri Lanka, Tanzania and Yemen apart from the new
members, was set up in March 1997 in Mauritius to promote economic
and trade cooperation among member countries.
</P>
<P>
All the current and future members of the IOR-ARC will sign an
instrument of accession, he said.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh's membership reflects the trust of confidence that
the country enjoys in the comity of other nations, and is a
tribute to the foreign policy of the Bangladeshi government which
has made efforts to promote intra- and inter-regional cooperation
for economic development as well as peace, progress and prosperity
of the region, said the foreign minister. 
</P>
</TEXT>
