<HEADLINE> China Starts Training Program for Local Chief Prosecutors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Chief prosecutors at local levels
in China started a one-year training program today.
</P>
<P>
Ninety local chief prosecutors were chosen to attend a model
training class which is being held in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
According to the plan of the Supreme People's Procuratorate (
SPP), all the chief prosecutors at the country's 3,700 prefecture
and county-level procuratorates will attend the course by rotation
during 1999.
</P>
<P>
"This training program is one of the most important measures to
advance the restructuring of China's prosecution system, and to
improve professional integrity of prosecutors and their competence.
" said Han Zhubin, procurator-general of the SPP, speaking at the
first lesson of the model class.
</P>
<P>
"It is aimed at arming top prosecutors at local levels with
firm ideological weapons and new working methods, because you
shoulder crucial responsibilities for the well-being of the
country's procutorial institutions," Han told the class.
</P>
<P>
The SPC will also spend three years training all its
prosecutors by rotation, according to Han. 
