<HEADLINE> China Issues Public Housing Fund Regulations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 8 (Xinhua) -- China has approved a set of
regulations on the building, management and supervision of the
public housing fund to ensure the smooth process of the housing
reform.
</P>
<P>
The public housing fund is created by contributions from
employers and employees. The employees are required to deposit a
certain portion of their salary into the fund.
</P>
<P>
The regulations stipulate that the fund is set up for the sole
purpose of purchasing, building, and renovating housing. But the
management center, an independent non-profit institution, can use
the fund to buy state debentures upon approval of a housing
committee composed of government officials, trade unions, and
experts.
</P>
<P>
According to the regulation, the public housing fund management
center's work is supervised by the financial departments of local
governments. In addition, employers and employees have the right
to be informed about the fund management. 
</P>
</TEXT>
