<HEADLINE> Defending Champion Gade Christensen Reaches Quarterfinals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 8 (Xinhua) -- World number one and top-seeded
Peter Gade Christensen of Denmark thrashed unseeded Chinese Taipei
player Chien Yu-hsiu 15-1, 15-3 here on Thursday to reach the
quarterfinals of the Japan Open Badminton Championships.
</P>
<P>
Gade Christensen, also the defending champion, spent only 29
minutes demolishing his opponent, ranked 166th in the world but a
15-10, 15-12 winner over ninth seed Dong Jiong of China in the
second round.
</P>
<P>
The Dane will next meet 12th seed Johan Hadi Kusuma of
Indonesia, a 15-8, 15-13 winner over his third-round opponent Ahn
Jae-chang of South Korea.
</P>
<P>
Elsewhere in the men's singles, fourth seed Sun Jun of China,
sixth-seeded Peter Rasmussen of Denmark and Malaysia's Ong Ewe
Hock, who is seeded 10th, are also through.
</P>
<P>
But the third-seeded Budi Santoso of Indonesia had a bad day,
losing 15-7, 17-14 to No. 11 seed Wong Choong Hann of Malaysia in
the third round.
</P>
<P>
Rasmussen is to take on 15th-seeded Chen Hong of China, while
Sun Jun takes on Ong Ewe Hock in the quarterfinals.
</P>
<P>
In the women's singles competition, defending champion Gong
Ruina of China outclassed Japan's Kaori Mori 11-2, 11-1 on a good
day for Chinese players.
</P>
<P>
Gong's teammate and third-seeded Ye Zhaoying scored an 11-1, 11-
6 victory over home player Kyoko Komuro to join other four Chinese
quarterfinalists, including No. 4 seed Zhou Mi, fifth seed Zhang
Ning and seventh-seeded Gong Zhichao.
</P>
<P>
Also advancing to the round of eight were Satomi Igawa and
sixth seed Yasuko Mizui of Japan, and South Korean Kim Ji-hyon.
</P>
<P>
On Friday, Mizui meets Gong Ruina, Kim plays Zhou, Igawa takes
on Gong Zhichao, and Zhang clashes with Ye in an all-Chinese
contest. 
</P>
</TEXT>
