<HEADLINE> Top Chinese Legislator Leaves Syria for Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, chairman of the
Standing Committee of the National People's Congress of China,
on Thursday concluded his three-day official visit to Syria and
left here for Islamabad, capital of Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
During his stay here, Li met with his Syrian counterpart or
President of the People's Council Abdel Kader Kaddura, Prime
Minister Mahmoud Zouebi, and President Hefez Al Assad. He
discussed with them the bilateral relations and regional and world
issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
The top Chinese legislator and the Syrian leaders agreed that
efforts should be made to further develop the bilateral relations
in the political, economic and trade, science and technological,
and cultural areas.
</P>
<P>
They also agreed that China and Syria should join hands in
promoting unity and cooperation among the developing countries
around the world, and in the efforts for pushing forward the
Middle East peace process and seeking a just and fair solution to
the Middle East issues.
</P>
<P>
Syria is the third leg of Li's six-nation tour across Europe
and Asia, which has already taken him to Greece and Turkey before
Syria, and will take him further on to Pakistan, Bangladesh, and
Thailand. 
</P>
</TEXT>
