<HEADLINE> Libya Calls on Foreign Oil Companies to Resume </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TUNIS, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Libya has appealed to foreign oil
companies to resume their activities in Libya after the United
Nations lifted sanctions on it.
</P>
<P>
Thursday's Libyan daily Al Arab quotes Libyan Minister of
Petroleum Abdalla Salem el-Badri as saying Wednesday Libya is also
ready to authorize companies from the United States, which still
maintains its sanctions on Libya, to resume operations.
</P>
