in Libya, the most important oil producing and exporting country
in north Africa.
</P>
<P>
After the handover of two Libyan suspects on April 5, the
U.N. Security Council decided to suspend the sanctions imposed on
Libya since 1992 for its alleged part in the bombing of a Pan Am
airliner over Lockerbie, Scotland in 1988, which killed 270
people. 
