<HEADLINE> 7 Abduction Suspects Arrested in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Seven suspects including a reserve
sub-inspector of police were arrested by Sri Lanka's special
police team Wednesday in connection with the abduction of a
millionaire, police sources said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the police also recovered over 17 million rupees
(242,857 U.S. dollars) from the possession of the suspects, the
sources said.
</P>
<P>
The millionaire, G. C. Wickremasinge, is former chairman of
Aitken Spence &AMP; Company.
</P>
<P>
He was abducted on the early morning of March 30 when he was on
his way to Colombo Golf links. Later the abductors demanded a
ransom of 20 million rupees (286,000 dollars) from his wife for
his release.
</P>
<P>
The ransom was paid the same night and the victim was released
the following morning.
</P>
<P>
The breakthrough came when police were tipped off by the
manager of the People's Bank Migallewa of Kurnegala that a sum of
290,000 rupees (4,142 dollars) all in one thousand rupee bills
bearing the identical serial numbers of the ransom money had been
deposited by a person, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Then the police team rushed to the bank and arrested the man,
the president of a farmers' organization, who deposited the money.
</P>
<P>
This led to the arrest of six others and police believed that
the reserve sub-inspector of police had led the group, the sources
added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
