<HEADLINE> Large State-Owned Enterprises Report Good Performances </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 8 (Xinhua) -- The 1998 annual reports of listed
companies on China's two stock exchanges indicate that the large
state-owned enterprises which have been listed since 1997
performed better last year than others.
</P>
<P>
By April 6, 441 companies listed on the Shanghai and Shenzhen
stock exchanges had published their annual reports, which show
that the average annual income per share stood at 0.3179 yuan,
with per-share net assets and net-asset return ratio averaging 2.
67 yuan and 11.94 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
But the per-share income, per-share net assets and net-asset
return ratio of the 25 large state-owned enterprises listed since
1997 averaged 0.4 yuan, 2.92 yuan and 13.75 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
According to today's Shanghai Securities News, nearly half of
the recently listed large state-owned enterprises increased their
profits in 1998 by 30 percent over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The recently listed large state-owned enterprises are mainly
engaged in metallurgy, energy, automobiles and public facilities.
</P>
</TEXT>
