<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 8 (Xinhua) -- A cholera outbreak in Nakuru of
Rift Valley Province in west Kenya has killed eight people in
last two days, according to the municipal medical authorities.
</P>
<P>
Local public health officer Jackson Njoroge said Wednesday that
the first case of cholera was reported last Sunday, the East
African Standard reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
