<HEADLINE> Map of HK Places of Interest to Be Available on Internet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 8 (Xinhua) -- The general public in Hong Kong
may find locations of places of interest on two websites in six
months' time thanks to a project named "Community Map on Internet".
</P>
<P>
The project, tendered out by the Lands Department of the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR), was awarded to a telecom
company and a property agency Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a contract signing ceremony Thursday, Secretary for
Information Technology and Broadcasting Kwong Ki-chi said the
project would provide an advanced and convenient system to help
people find their way around Hong Kong, both for work and for
leisure.
</P>
<P>
Building on the basis of the digital maps the Lands Department
has developed, the websites will show locations of public
facilities, transport routes and other premises such as shops,
restaurants and cinemas on the maps.
</P>
<P>
The Lands Department has established its computerized mapping
system for several years. By utilizing the state-of-the-art
geographic information system technology, it has been producing up-
to-date and versatile digital maps covering the SAR.
</P>
<P>
In September last year, it launched the "Computerized Map
Inquiry System for Tourists on Internet" project together with the
Hong Kong Tourist Association to meet the needs of tourists.
</P>
</TEXT>
