<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 8 (Xinhua)-- Chinese consumers are complaining
most about the quality of goods, poor services and mail-order,
according to the Chinese Consumers Association.
</P>
<P>
So far this year, the association has received nearly 140,000
letters of complaints, 68 percent dealing with the quality of
goods, with shoes topping the list.
</P>
<P>
