<HEADLINE> Air Strikes on Yugoslavia to Continue Methodically: France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 8 (Xinhua) -- French Defense Minister Alain
Richard said on Thursday that the NATO airstrikes against
Yugoslavia will continue methodically.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with France Inter radio station, Richard said
the proposal on unilateral cease-fire in Kosovo by Belgrade
indicated that the power of Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic
was beginning to "crack" in front of a "total deletion of his
military potential."
</P>
<P>
