infrastructures, and the capacities of commanding" of the Yugoslav
forces, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said the means of Yugoslav ground troops remained relatively
unattacked because of the presence of civilians.
</P>
<P>
The defense minister estimated that "progressive and controlled
steps in military strikes ... are the most rapid and most
efficient way" to achieve the goal of NATO.
</P>
<P>
"The objective is ... to give the people the right to live in
Kosovo in peace," he said. 
