<HEADLINE> Violent Incidents Kill 3 in Manila </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Three persons were killed and three
others wounded in separate shooting and stabbing incidents
Wednesday in Quezon City of Manila, the Philippine News Agency
said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Initial probe conducted by the police showed that the six
people were attacked at between 5:30 and 6 p.m. Wednesday, when a
birthday party was being held in the Maligaya Park Subdivision and
the unidentified suspects were armed with knives and homemade
shotgun.
</P>
<P>
Motives of the shooting and stabbing are still being determined
by the police and no arrests have been made yet. 
</P>
