<DOCNO> XIE19990408.0246 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fresh Clash Hits Indonesian W. Kalimantan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 8 (Xinhua) -- An angry mob on Thursday attacked
Abdul Azis General Hospital in the riot-torn West Kalimantan town
of Singkawang, Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
This attack shocked patients, doctors and paramedics, Antara
News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
But no casualties and material damage were reported in the
violence.
</P>
<P>
Previously, a group of local people also attacked a police
precinct in Singkawang district. They demanded the release of tens
of detained rioters.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, Malays and Dayaks in the village of We Sungai of the
district clashed with Madurese. Over a dozen houses were burned
during the violence, but no casualties were reported.
</P>
<P>
The police detained 56 people suspected of being involved in
the clash. 
</P>
</TEXT>
