<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yunnan Province Starts Major Environmental Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Yunnan Province
has launched an ambitious environmental project to clean up all
the waters and afforest all the mountains.
</P>
<P>
Since last year's devastating floods in many parts of China,
which killed 3,004 people and brought more than 200 billion yuan
in losses, the central government has given top priority to
environmental and ecological programs. Land erosion has been
identified as a major cause for the devastating floods.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan is a mountainous area and has been included in a state
program to curb severe soil erosion along the Yangtze River.
Surveys have discovered that 37 percent of all the land in the
province is now suffering from serious erosion.
</P>
<P>
Under this new program, local people will further transform
cultivated lands, plant trees and grass, build small water
conservancy projects, and carry out other ecological projects.
</P>
<P>
According to local officials, six billion yuan has been spent
by the province to curb soil erosion over the past decade, during
which more than 400,000 projects have been implemented to control
erosion over an area of 22,000 square kilometers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
