<HEADLINE> Yangshao Culture Relics Unearthed in Shaanxi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Eight cultural relics, which are
believed to date back to the Yangshao Culture period, have been
unearthed recently around the Qiaoshan Mountains, about 200 km
northeast of Xi'an, the capital of Shaanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
They include various pottery items, bricks, tiles and the
remains of old city walls and are scattered over an area of 40 sq
km.
</P>
<P>
The discovery demonstrates that primitive tribes lived in the
area during the Yangshao Culture period which dates back 5,000 to
7,000 years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
