<HEADLINE> China Reports Rapid Industrial Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 8 (Xinhua) -- China had 10.1 percent growth in
industrial added value in the first quarter of this year,
according to National Statistics Bureau (NBS).
</P>
<P>
The country's incremental output value was 447 billion yuan for
the period. In March, the figure was 167 billion yuan, up 9
percent from March of last year.
</P>
<P>
The January-March period had incremental output value in the
state sector that was up 8.3 percent to 257.5 billion yuan. In
collectively-owned firms it was up 8.5 percent and in foreign-
funded companies, 13.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
Heavy industry has been the major beneficiary of the
government's large investment in infrastructure. In the January-
March period, heavy industry had 259.5 billion yuan in incremental
value, up 10.5 percent from the same period last year. Refined oil
output increased 7.6 percent and steel, 8.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
There was 187.5 billion yuan of light industrial incremental
value for the period, up 9.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
Production of some electric appliances and telecommunications
products grew rapidly during the period. Refrigerator output was
up 16.2 percent and air conditioner output, 70.2 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
