<HEADLINE> Wal-Mart Expanding China Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Wal-Mart, the world's largest
chain-store operator, is increasing investment in China after two
years of successful business here.
</P>
<P>
It has added 40 million U.S. dollars in investment to set up 5
stores in the booming Pearl River Delta area in Guangdong Province.
They are expected to increase China sales by 1.5 billion yuan
annually.
</P>
<P>
Wal-Mart came to Shenzhen in 1996, establishing a joint venture
with the Shenzhen International Investment and Trust Co. and
investing in 4 department stores and a warehouse store that sell
some 20,000 different kinds of goods.
</P>
<P>
It has invested 112 million U.S. dollars in China and had sales
of 361 million dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
