<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kournikova Beats Capriati at Amelia Island </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Ninth seed Anna Kournikova of
Russia beat American Jennifer Capriati 6-3, 6-3 to advance to the
round of 16 at the Bausch &AMP; Lomb Championships in Amelia Island,
Florida, on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Kournikova trailed 3-2 in the first set and 2-0 in the second,
but rallied both times on the clay surface to win the next four
games and regain control of the match.
</P>
<P>
Capriati, now ranked 81st in the world, was ranked as high as
sixth in the world in 1991, reached the Wimbledon and U.S. Open
semifinals as a 15-year-old. But she suffered from burnout by 1993
and was later arrested for drug possession, forcing her off the
women's tour for two years
</P>
<P>
Kournikova will next take on top-seeded Lindsay Davenport of
the United States, who had the day off after winning her second-
round match on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In other matches, defending champion and fourth seed Mary
Pierce of France cruised to a 6-0, 6-0 victory over Romania's
Catalina Cristea. Fifth-seeded Amanda Coetzer of South Africa and
10th-seeded Chanda Rubin of the United States also advanced with
straight-set victories.
</P>
<P>
But 13th seed Lisa Raymond and 16th seed Iva Majoli of Croatia
faded in the third sets of their matches.
</P>
<P>
Raymond won only six points in the deciding set as the 25-year-
old American was eliminated by Colombia's Fabiola Zuluaga 6-2, 5-7,
6-0. Majoli, the 1997 French Open champion, fell 3-6, 6-4, 6-2 to
Argentina's Ines Gorrochategui. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
