<HEADLINE> Grant Hill Leads Pistons Past Hawks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Grant Hill scored 15 of his 30
points in the fourth quarter to lead Detroit Pistons to a 89-82
win over the visiting Atlanta Hawks 89-82 on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Hill, who missed two shots and a pair of free throws in the
final minute of Monday's loss to Indiana, came up big in the final
12 minutes of this game. He scored eight of the Pistons' first 11
points in the final period, including an 18-footer that gave them
a 79-69 lead with 5:54 to play.
</P>
<P>
Bison Dele added 18 points for the Pistons, who have won seven
of the last eight home meetings with Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
At New Jersey, Eric Snow made a driving layup with 1:19
remaining to lift the Philadelphia 76ers to a 96-92 victory over
the Nets and into eighth place in the Eastern Conference.
</P>
<P>
The Sixers moved past the New York Knicks and Cleveland
Cavaliers into the final playoff spot in the East.
</P>
<P>
In Charlotte, the Knicks scored just 12 points in the first
quarter, fell behind by 17 and were embarrassed by the Hornets 106-
82, further hampering their playoff chances in what was once a
season of high expectations.
</P>
<P>
Bobby Phills scored 18 points for the Hornets, who broke a five-
game losing streak.
</P>
<P>
In the other games, Milwaukee Bucks beat Cleveland Cavaliers 99-
91, Boston Celtics crushed Washington Wizards 108-87, Indiana
Pacers overpowered the slumping Chicago Bulls 91-74, Los Angeles
Lakers defeated Sacramento Kings 104-89, Phoenix Suns routed
Minnesota Timberwolves 90-82, Miami Heat ousted Dallas Mavericks
93-87 and Denver Nuggets edged Vancouver Grizzlies 87-84. 
</P>
</TEXT>
