<HEADLINE> Housing Sales Up In Guangdong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 8 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangdong Province
has seen its efforts to reform its housing sector begin to pay off
as sales rose at an annual rate of 28 percent by the end of last
year.
</P>
<P>
According to Construction Department figures, the province sold
12 million sq.m. of apartments last year, up 26 percent from the
previous year, about 78 percent of which was bought by individuals.
</P>
<P>
Banks in Guangdong issued 15 billion yuan in individual
mortgage loans last year to aid home purchases, double the amount
for 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
