<HEADLINE> Australian-Funded Poverty-Relief Project Launched </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, April 8 (Xinhua) -- A major poverty-elimination
program funded by the Australian government has been initiated in
the Qianjiang Development Zone in southwest China's Chongqing
Municipality.
</P>
<P>
The project, at a cost of 120 million yuan, is the largest
Australian-funded poverty-relief program in China.
</P>
<P>
The funds will be used for a number of projects including rural
roads, drinking-water facilities, disease control, professional
training, and education.
</P>
<P>
Qianjiang is one of the poorest areas in the country. 
</P>
