<HEADLINE> Polish Deputies Oppose Poland Joining NATO Action </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, April 7 (Xinhua) -- A parliamentary delegation of the
Polish Peasant Party declared here Wednesday that it was against
Poland's participation in NATO's military action in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
The delegation made the declaration soon after it ended a
meeting on Polish foreign policies.
</P>
<P>
"It will be a wrong decision if Poland sends its forces to
Kosovo," the official Polish news agency quoted a delegation head
as saying.
</P>
<P>
He said NATO failed to employ all chances to find a peaceful
settlement to the crisis before it started bombing Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
He accused NATO of violating the U.N. Charter by bombing a
sovereign state.
</P>
<P>
"If we say Serbs have hurt the feelings of ethnic Albanians in
Kosovo, NATO air raids brought more damage to them," he noted.
</P>
<P>
He also admitted there were differences within his party over
NATO military actions in Yugoslavia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
