<HEADLINE> EDS-Details Added Chinese President Meets Mexican Defense Secretary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
President Jiang extended welcome to Cervantes and asked the
defense secretary to convey his greeting to Mexican President
Ernesto Zedillo Ponce de Leon, saying that he was satisfied with
the growth of bilateral relations after the forging of diplomatic
ties between the two countries 27 years ago.
</P>
<P>
"The frequent state-to-state and army-to-army contacts in
recent years have given an impetus to the development of bilateral
relationship and to the links between the armed forces of the two
countries," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Cervantes transferred the greeting from President Zedillo to
President Jiang, saying that it was his years' wish to visit China,
a country with an ancient civilization. The People's Liberation
Army (PLA) is a great army and he could learn a lot from it, he
added.
</P>
<P>
He said his ongoing visit to China is aimed at furthering the
development of friendly and cooperative ties between the two armed
forces.
</P>
<P>
Chi Haotian, vice chairman of the Central Military Commission,
State Councilor and Defense Minister, and other senior officers
were present at the meeting. 
</P>
