<HEADLINE> Tornado Lashes Northwestern Bangladesh, Six Killed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Six people has been killed and 100
injured in a northwester accompanied by hailstorm lashing Dinajpur
and Lalmonirhat districts in northwest Bangladesh, press reports
here said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The tornado, hitting the two districts on Tuesday night,
damaged about 3,500 houses rendering hundreds of people homeless,
witnesses were quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Five people died in house collapses and lightning when the
hailstorm pounded Dinajpur, while thunderbolt struck another man
to death as the tropical storm lashed Lalmonirhat.
</P>
<P>
Extensive damages were caused to standing irrigational paddy
crops by the hailstorm, and 12 33-kv electric towers were
uprooted, forcing suspension of power supply in the area. The
restoration of power supply would take at least one week,
officials said.
</P>
<P>
In Rangpur district, some 260 kilometers northwest of here,
about 200 thatched houses and a vast tract of standing rice crops
were damaged in the northwester which also uprooted many tress and
disrupted power supply in the town and its adjoining areas.
</P>
</TEXT>
