<HEADLINE> EDS-rpt with change in 4th para European Nations Offer Aid to Kosovo Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
 VIENNA, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Some European countries have
offered aid to the Kosovo refugees, including food, medicine, and
materials for building camps to shelter tens of thousands living
in overcrowded conditions in Albania.
</P>
<P>
Austria on Wednesday approved a plan offering about 40 million
U.S. dollars to set up an Austrian camp in Albania to shelter the
Kosovo refugees. The government has also decided to take 5,000
refugees into Austria.
</P>
<P>
Hungary has reportedly shipped 50 tons of aid which includes
food, medicine and carpets to refugees in Albania.
</P>
<P>
Ethnic Albanians are fleeing war from Kosovo in large numbers
since NATO started bombing Yugoslavia on March 24 to force
Belgrade to agree to a peace plan for Kosovo, where the majority
of the population is Albanian.
</P>
<P>
Sweden has also sent a 30-vehicle convoy of humanitarian aid
Monday to the Kosovo refugees in Albania.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Italian government is planning to build camps
in Albania to house about 25,000 Kosovo refugees, said a press
release by the Ylberi Coordination Center.
</P>
<P>
The Center was formed by representatives of the Italian
Embassy, the Special Diplomatic Delegation, the Delegation of
Experts, the Interforze Delegation of Italian Police and Civil
Defense.
</P>
<P>
The Center will set up an army field hospital before April 9,
in which 100 patients can simultaneously receive medical treatment,
said the press. 
</P>
</TEXT>
