<HEADLINE> China Now 8th In Total Length Of Expressways </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 8 (Xinhua) -- China now has 6,258 kilometers of
expressways, putting it ahead of Japan and the country with the 8
th longest system of expressways in the world.
</P>
<P>
It has 12,600 kilometers of expressways under construction,
according to the Economic Daily.
</P>
<P>
China began building expressways in the mid '80s. The first,
the 18.5-km. Shanghai-Jiading expressway, was completed on October
31, 1988.
</P>
<P>
On September 1, 1990, a 375-kilometer expressway linking
Shenyang and Dalian in northeastern China, opened to traffic. In
1993, the first expressway built with World Bank loans, between
Beijing, Tianjin, and Tanggu, was completed.
</P>
<P>
The expressways have been a vital means of alleviating traffic
problems between major cities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
