<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Arrives in Washington </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji
arrived here from Los Angeles Wednesday by special plane to
continue his eight-day official visit to the United States at the
invitation of President Bill Clinton.
</P>
<P>
Zhu, who arrived in Los Angeles Tuesday to kick off the visit,
is the first Chinese premier to visit the country in 15 years.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Washington, the Chinese premier is expected
to have an extensive and in-depth exchange of views with Clinton
on Sino-U.S. ties as well as major international and regional
issues of common concern. Zhu will also co-chair the second
meeting of the China-U.S. Environment and Development Forum with
Vice-President Al Gore.
</P>
<P>
The plane landed at the Andrews Air Base at 17:30 (local time),
and Zhu and his wife, Lao An, were given a red-carpet welcome.
</P>
<P>
Present at the air base to welcome Zhu and his wife were U.S.
Secretary of the Housing and Urban Development Andrew Cuomo, U.S.
Ambassador to China James Sasser and Mrs. Sasser as well as other
U.S. officials.
</P>
<P>
Long Yongtu, chief negotiator of the Ministry of the Foreign
Trade and Economic Cooperation who arrived in Washington earlier,
greeted the Chinese Premier at the air base.
</P>
<P>
Also present were over 350 representatives of the local Chinese
community and Chinese students studying in the country.
</P>
<P>
Zhu's entourage included State Councilor Wu Yi, State Councilor
and Secretary-General of the State Council Wang Zhongyu, Foreign
Minister Tang Jiaxuan, Minister in charge of the State Development
Planning Commission Zeng Peiyan, and Minister of Foreign Trade and
Economic Cooperation Shi Guangsheng.
</P>
<P>
Washington is the second leg of Zhu's official visit to the
United States. 
</P>
</TEXT>
