<HEADLINE> China Cracking Down On Issuing Of False Invoices </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 8 (Xinhua) -- China's State Administration of
Taxation (SAT) is taking steps to control invoices with a
nationwide check on bogus invoices from April to June.
</P>
<P>
An SAT official says that this is a way of combating the misuse
and falsification of invoices and one of the most important
weapons in the fight against tax evasion that has resulted in a
loss of tax revenues.
</P>
<P>
The check will be carried out in three steps: internal
inspection of invoice offices and individuals; an inspection by
tax officials; and straightening out penalties and requirements.
The administration will investigate all value-added tax (VAT)
payments and the entire invoice procedure will be revised to
comply with SAT requirements.
</P>
<P>
The state has reported that 62 people have been sentenced to
death in China over the past 5 years for charges related to VAT
invoices. 
</P>
</TEXT>
