<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia to Review Disarmament Plan: Defense Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The defense minister, who returned from Tajikstan Wednesday,
told the press that Russia would increase the size of its 1.2
million-strong armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Russia decided to reinforce its combat forces because NATO
intends to implement a new strategy in which the bloc may use
force in any place without approval from the United Nations,
Sergeyev said.
</P>
<P>
He said that he and President Boris Yeltsin were concerned
about NATO's new strategy, noting that their "worries" were
confirmed by NATO's military actions against Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
The defense minister warned that if NATO launched a ground war
in Yugoslavia, the Kosovo conflict is likely to spread beyond
Yugoslav territory.
</P>
<P>
Sergeyev believed NATO's aggression against Yugoslavia has
undermined the Russia-NATO relationship established within the
framework of a "peaceful partnership plan."
</P>
<P>
Under the current situation, it is impossible for Russia's
State Duma (lower house of parliament) to ratify the Russia-U.S.
START-II nuclear weapons treaty, Sergeyev said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
