<HEADLINE> Liaoning Province Restoring Old Palace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Shenyang, the capital of
northeast China's Liaoning province, plans to restore part of its
old palace before early May.
</P>
<P>
Plans call for the ground around the Dazheng Hall (Major
Affairs Hall) to be lowered and tiles to be replaced so that the
cornerstones and steps can be seen and the hall regain its
original look.
</P>
<P>
Renovation efforts in the past caused the ground around the
Dazheng to be raised to make the floor level with the surrounding
area, affecting the overall looks of the buildings.
</P>
<P>
A study has shown that the original ground was half a meter
lower than the current ground level around the Dazheng, which was
built between 1621 and 1628. The hall was used for state
ceremonies by the Qing Dynasty. 
</P>
</TEXT>
