<DOCNO> XIE19990408.0338 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippine  Banks' Reserves Cut by One Percentage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Philippine Central Bank Governor
Gabriel Singson announced Wednesday a one percentage point cut in
banks' reserve requirements effective April 15, Malaya newspaper
reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The governor also reported that the Monetary Board of the
Central Bank has approved the exemption from the required
loan-loss provisions all loans given out after March 31 this year.
</P>
<P>
The two moves will hopefully stimulate the economy by
encouraging banks to resume lending.
</P>
<P>
The one percentage point cut will be done on the liquidity
reserve requirement currently set at five percent.
</P>
<P>
Thus the reserves against deposits will be set at 14 percent
effective in mid April.
</P>
<P>
The cut will free another 11 billion pesos (47.5 million U.S.
dollars) for banks to lend to customers.
</P>
<P>
The government was encouraged to order another cut in reserves
after the March inflation rate dropped sharply to 8.7 percent from
9.9 percent in February. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
