<HEADLINE> Twenty Wounded in Argentine Subway Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENAS AIRES, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Twenty people were injured in
a subway accident on Wednesday involving two trains in Palermo
station, in Buenos Aires, said police sources.
</P>
<P>
The accident happened when a running train collided with
another stationary train in the station of Palermo.
</P>
<P>
The people suffered light injuries and panic spread throughout
the passengers, added the same source.
</P>
<P>
The accident caused transit problems in the area and the
principal routes connecting with the centre of the city.
</P>
<P>
The undergound train accident which occured on Wednesday is the
third since the service was privatized in Argentina.
</P>
<P>
The most tragic underground accident occurred on March 26, 1985
on the same line, when four people died and 34 were injured.
</P>
