<HEADLINE> Guangdong Province Smashes Smuggling Rings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 8 (Xinhua) -- Last year, the Customs Office of
Guangdong Province dealt with 5,600 smuggling cases, seizing
illegal goods valued at 4.9 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
A local Customs official said that the number of smuggling
cases had increased by 5.1 percent last year.
</P>
<P>
The province initiated a series of anti-smuggling projects
early last year, he said, adding that goods seized in these cases
included refined-oil, foreign currency, and pornographic or
pirated CDs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
