<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Defending Champions Argentina Beaten by Ghana </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Defending champions Argentina
suffered a surprise 1-0 defeat against Ghana in soccer's world
youth championship on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Hosts Nigerian "Flying Eagles" created another African surprise
by beating Germany 2-0 in a tension-soaked match.
</P>
<P>
Mexico became the first team to ensure a second-round berth by
beating Austrlia 3-1, Croatia breezed past Kazakhstan 5-1, and
Ireland and Paraguay both won for the first time, beating Saudi
Arabia and Costa Rica respectively.
</P>
<P>
A late goal by Peter Ofari-Quaye gave Ghana victory in the
group B game in Kaduna against Argentina, who have won the last
two world youth championships.
</P>
<P>
Ofari-Quaye, Ghana's most dangerous player and scorer of their
goal in their opening 1-1 draw with Croatia, breached the
Argentine defence in the 77th minute and scored with a left foot
shot.
</P>
<P>
Croatia gave Kazakhstan their second straight defeat in the
match. The goals were scored by Zvonimir Deranja, Silvester
Sabolcki, Ivica Banovic and Sasa Bjelanovic.
</P>
<P>
Kazakhstan's Ali Aliyec scored an own goal while Yerlan
Urazayev grabbed their consolation and only goal of the tournament.
</P>
<P>
Second-half goals by Ganiyu Shittu and Hashimu Garba downed the
Germans, who were without Enrico Kern, their hat-trick hero
against Paraguay on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Paraguay then overcame Costa Rica 3-1 thanks to goals from
Roque Santa Cruz, Nelson Vera and Nelson Cuevas.
</P>
<P>
A spectacular long-range goal by Stephan McPhail and a Damien
Duff effort gave Ireland their 2-0 win over Saudi Arabia, who
missed a second-half penalty and had a first-half goal disallowed.
</P>
</TEXT>
