<HEADLINE> Argentina Stock Closes High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The Burenos Aires stock
market closed up on wednesday of 2.34 percent on the leading
shares of the Marval index, at 449.97 points.
</P>
<P>
The interbank exchange rates Wednesday reduced to 5.50 percent
annually on the 24 hour term against the previous 5.60 percent,and
the parity the peso against the dollar maintained itself at 0.997
pesos to the dollar on purchase and 1.002 on sale.
</P>
<P>
Anaylsts here said that Argentine stock maintains high
reflecting the influence of Dow Jones index's soaring to 10,085.59
points on Wednesday. 
