<HEADLINE> NATO Bombs Downtown Belgrade Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, April 7 (Xinhua) -- A NATO bomb blasted on top of a
government building in downtown Belgrade late Wednesday,
shattering glasses on the doors and windows of the building and
nearby buildings.
</P>
<P>
The blast took place around 11:20 pm local time according to
eyewitnesses.
</P>
<P>
The building, located within 500 meters from the city's railway
station, was the old parliamentary building which had been
deserted.
</P>
<P>
No casualty was reported by the police who had cordoned off the
area of the blast.
</P>
<P>
Fire engines rushed to the spot but there was no flame in the
building.
</P>
<P>
This was the third time NATO has attacked downtown Belgrade.
NATO cruise missiles and bombs blasted two government buildings on
April 3 and a heating plant on April 4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
