<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazil's Stocks Soar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO April 7 (Xinhua) -- Stocks on Brazil's Sao Paulo
exchange, the largest in Latin America, Wednesday closed soaring
with the benchmark Bovesa index of 11,529 points, a 3.26 percent
increase against Tuesday's 11,165 points.
</P>
<P>
The turnover was some 557 million dollars against 520 million
dollars on Tuesday. It was the largest volum traded this year.
</P>
<P>
In Rio de Janeiro, the stocks also closed higher at 39,357
points against Tuesday's 38,335 points. or 2.6 percent higher.
</P>
<P>
Economists said stocks soaring reflected the recovery of
confidence of investors in Brazil.
</P>
<P>
Just before the closing of the stocks, Brazil's President
Fernando Henrique Cardoso said that his country's economy is
emerging from a prolonged crisis stronger than before. 
</P>
</TEXT>
