<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Philippine Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 8 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items
in leading Philippine newspapers Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Manila Bulletin:
</P>
<P>
-- The Philippine President Estrada demanded Wednesday that the
National Democratic Front proves its sincerity in its public
statements that it would release the five police and military
officers it abducted and is now holding as hostages.
</P>
<P>
Manila Standard:
</P>
<P>
-- American financial giant Citibank NA is convinced the
Philippines continues to be one of the top investment destinations
for multinational companies because of its stable political
environment and competitive labor force.
</P>
<P>
Malaya:
</P>
<P>
-- President Estrada said Wednesday the crime of death convicts
Dante Piandong, Jesus Morallos and Archie Bulan are "not so
heinous" and their sentence may be commuted to life imprisonment
if it is proven they had no idea the victim they shot dead was a
policeman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
