<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canada to Provide Food Aid for Kosovar Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, April 7 (Xinhua) -- Canada would provide 5 million
Canadian dollars (3.3 million U.S. dollars) in food aid to the
Kosovar refugees, Canadian International Cooperation Minister
Diane Marleau announced Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Canada, through the Canadian International Development Agency
(CIDA), will be providing canned fish and other commodities such
as vegetable oil, to the refugees through the World Food
Programme(WFP).
</P>
<P>
The food aid is in addition to the 10 million Canadian dollars
in humanitarian assistance announced last week by the minister,
bringing Canada's aid for the refugees from Kosovo to 15 million
Canadian dollars since March 30.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
