<BODY>
<HEADLINE> First Refugees Arrive in Germany, More Expected </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bonn, April 7 (xinhua) -- An airbus plane of the German forces
landed in Nuremberg Wednesday afternoon with 60 refugees from
Kosovo, the first batch to reach the country in a program that is
just getting underway.
</P>
<P>
Among the refugees aboard the plane from the Macedonian capital
of Skopje were 50 women and children and 10 men who had been
picked up by the United Nations (U.N.) High Commission for
Refugees on the basis of need.
</P>
<P>
Until Thursday morning, a total of 600 refugees will be brought
to Germany by the planes of German forces and the airline
corporation Lufthansa, officials said.
</P>
<P>
The first refugees will be sent to the states of Bavaria,
Hamburg, Schleswig-Holstein, North Rhine-Westphalia, and Lower
Saxonia, where they will be permitted a 3 month residence.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
