<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dow Hits New Record on Wall Street </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MEW YORK, April 7 (Xinhua) -- The Dow Jones industrial
average hit the record high Wednesday as aluminum maker
Alcoa reported its good earnings in the first quarter.
</P>
<P>
The Dow closed up 121.82 at 10,085.31, finishing above
10,000 points for the third time since March 29 when the index
broke the five digit milestone for the first time in the
closing session. The blue chip stocks set its previous closing
record of 10,007.33 on April 5.
</P>
<P>
The index opened strongly as Alcoa, a component of the
Dow, said that its first-quarter earnings beat investors'
expectations. The good news pushed the Alcoa stock up and
helped other blue-chips move higher as well.
</P>
<P>
But the pessimistic analysis of high-tech sector drove
the Nasdaq index lower. The technology heavy composite fell
18.74 at 2,544.43.
</P>
<P>
Analysts from Merrill Lynch warned that the high-tech
sector would have some tough time ahead. The warning hit the
commuter market.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index was up 9.00 at 1,326.89
and the NYSE index was up 3.91 at 616.23. The American Stock
Exchange index was up 2.09 at 717.30.
</P>
<P>
The Russell 2000 index of smaller companies fell 3.31 at
397.77.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by an 8-to-7 margin
on the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,600 up, 1,381 down and
567 unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume increased to 813.36 million shares from 785.88
million in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
